            <div class="md:col-span-2 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-8 border-t-4 border-denton-blue">
                <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-denton-blue">The Power of Texas Education Code §54.353</h2>
                    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-2">This state law authorizes the Firefighters Enrolled in Fire Science Courses program, providing a full exemption from tuition and lab fees for eligible firefighters pursuing approved fire science curricula at public institutions.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-denton-red text-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg text-center transform hover:scale-105 transition-transform">
                    <p class="text-6xl md:text-7xl font-black">$0</p>
                    <p class="text-2xl font-bold">TUITION & LABS</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-denton-blue mb-4 text-center">Eligibility: Who Qualifies?</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 text-center">The program serves both paid and volunteer firefighters who meet specific criteria.</p>
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-denton-red mb-2">Paid Firefighters</h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-gray-700">
                            <li>Must be employed as a paid, full-time firefighter.</li>
                            <li>Employer must be a political subdivision of Texas (e.g., city, county).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-denton-red mb-2">Volunteer Firefighters</h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-gray-700">
                            <li>Must be an active member for at least one year.</li>
                            <li>Department must participate in a state-approved retirement system.</li>
                            <li>Must hold an Accredited Advanced cert from SFFMA or a Phase V (Firefighter II) cert from TCFP.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-denton-red mb-2">Academic Requirements</h4>
                         <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside text-gray-700">
                            <li>Must enroll in courses within an approved Fire Science curriculum.</li>
                             <li>Must maintain Satisfactory Academic Progress (SAP).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 flex flex-col justify-center">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-denton-blue mb-4 text-center">The Educational Landscape</h3>
